annotation.TEXT: There's those silver munchers again. I have a bad feeling about them, so I'm going to just avoid touching them altogether, even though I have Yoshi.
Oh, I bet there's something good on the lower route, but that jump looks a little tricky...
Alright, he can eat the sideways piranha plants. I think I remember playing a hack before where Yoshi couldn't eat those for some reason.
And, just like before, the screen won't scroll back.
Well, so much for that plan...

1 vote for the square root of minus one divided by zero, 1 vote for the ghost house's secret exit (sorry, but I couldn't find any), 1 vote for the opposite of what everyoneï»¿ wants, 1 vote for Bowser's Castle, 1 vote for 3-5, 2 votes for 42, 2 votes for 3-1, 3 votes for 3-4, and 5 votes for 3-3! So, I'll do 3-3 next!
Those spike tops aren't much of a threat. In fact, whenever they go offscreen vertically, they disappear and are treated as dead by the game. I wonder why...
Wait, maybe I can use the sprite limit to my advantage. If I fry enough of them and don't collect their coins...
Alright, let's play Rabbit Forest 5 while I'm on a roll here. It's a red level, so keep an eye out for a secret exit.
Ooh, another retro level!
Is he just going to jump off the bottom of the screen? Yep!
Once again, it's nice to be able to change power ups on the fly.
Okay, with 3-3 clear, let's move on to 3-4, which appears to possibly be a water level.
Oh! Hi, Yoshi! Glad to see you here!
Watch out! It's a rainbow shell!
Wow, that was one of the most pathetic attempts at the goal tape I have ever made!
And, just like before, there's a glitch that lets me scroll backwards a little bit at a time just after I come out of the pipe, but once again, I'm not going to waste time with it.
The screen stopped scrolling. So, do I enter the castle door? Or...
I kind of want a flower, but I'll take a spare cape for now.
There's the last Yoshi coin, so I gotta be nearing the end...
Yes, alright!
Oh, wow is he glitched! I'm pretty sure Hammer Bros. don't normally bury themselves like that!
Oh, we've got these types of pipes, eh? Interesting...
Oh, good. They stopped.
Oh, crap! Not these guys!
Well, that's it for this level. I like these retro levels. I hope there's an SMB2-themed level at some point.
Level complete! And I lined up the numbers for a useless 1-up! Yay!
But, alright! We got Yoshi back!
Well, that wasn't so bad. Maybe a little on the boring side...
Nuts, I keep missing. Ehh, it's probably easier to just bump him off from below.
Uh, oh. This could be tricky. Or I could just swat the thing with my cape.
This one takes place underground.
And there'd better be something in that pipe over there, because I'm not getting back otherwise!
Yeah, I'll play it safe and go with the cape here.
Aha! Anything further to the right?
Argh! That was me being stupid!
Yeah, I figured it was a changing tide level, just like Mondo.
To be continued...
I figured there was a secret there!
What's with the gray sky? Also, I'm not sure if that water below is swimmable or just a bottomless pit (probably the latter), so I'm not going to take any chances.
I hope there's a flower in one of those...
Another Yoshi's House? Well, I'll go there another time. For right now, let's go back and get the normal exit from 3-5...
However, since I got Yoshi back...

...I can now fly to other worlds again, which means you can vote on worlds 4, 5, or 6 as well! (Also, Zeldara109 reminded me of that level between worlds 1 and 2 that required at least one active switch to do anything with. You can vote on that level as well if you want.)
Nope. How about if I go to the right instead?
Uhh... Why is he stuck in the ground? ...Hahaha!!!
Of course the pipe leads somewhere. This game isn't that mean! (I think...)
Hello, and welcome back to Super SIG World 21! Let's take a look at the voting results this time...
Okay, it's only partially submerged, so I'm going to be optimistic and think of it as half-empty... wait...
It's the key! Now, where's the keyhole? Is it over the top to the left?
Oh, end of the level already? Not quite. Them staircases like to fool you like that.
Whoa. Good thing I had a cape to glide down slowly and see where to land there!
Uh, oh. Autoscrolling. I wonder how nasty this'll be...
Whoa, almost got a spike in the butt there.

So, your choices are: 3-Castle, 3-Yoshi's House, 4-1, 5-1, 6-1, and that level between worlds 1 and 2. The winner will be what I start with next time! (Also, 3-YH will probably be a single screen level, so if that wins, I'll do the runner up right afterwards. Or you could vote on a second level after 3-YH. That'll work too.)
Oh, I can't walk through these tree trunks. I'll have to go below.
Nope. The screen stops scrolling at this point. So, let's just unlock this secret exit...
BARF! That's okay. I've still got two feathers! (If you're gonna get hit, it may as well be at a time that it doesn't really matter!)
Wait, what am I watching out for again?
Missed that coin, but since I can't scroll back, we won't be seeing that piranha plant again anyway.
Ah, okay. I just keep going to the right to transition to the next area.
Uh, oh. Well, I'll just float over that guy and fry him from behind with my flower... Huh?
Oh, I see an opening that I can fly to up there!
Better be careful. Some bullet cannons are stacked on top of each other, like you'd often see in SMB's 7-1.
And that unlocks the castle. So, for next time, you can vote on the castle or that Yoshi's House (or whatever it's actually called) over there.
